@vrv In the PR the `third_party/boringssl/add_boringssl_s390x.patch` file has been deleted.

In `tensorflow/workspace.bzl` file, the boringssl section has been changed from `patched_http_archive` -> `native.http_archive` so patching is gone.

Also, in case `s390x` support is desired in TensorFlow in the future, from the comment link provided (https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/pull/11170#issuecomment-329252942) it is possible to disable the GCP support to handle the big-endian issue. I don't have any access to `s390x` so I might not be able to help in that case though.
